abstract.value: Anne Dockery was a photographer with Liberation News Service. This collection consists of her black and white photographic prints of various sizes, film negatives, and color slides.

p.value: Identification of item, date; Anne Dockery Photographs; TAM 743; box number; folder number; Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives, New York University.
Materials found in repository; provenance is unknown.

This collection consists of black and white photographic prints of various sizes, film negatives, and color slides all created by Anne Dockery, a photographer with Liberation News Service. Subjects include anti-Vietnam War marches, Gay Pride marches, Black Panthers demonstrations, the Republican National Convention, plus New York City, Northern Ireland, Hanoi, London, and Vermont.
